# React + TypeScript Patterns

## Components

- Functional components only — no class components
- **Use named exports** for React components and pages (`export function Foo` / `export const Foo`), not `export default`
- Exception: Vite/Electron config files may keep `export default` (tooling convention)
- Define props as an `interface` named `{Component}Props`
- Destructure props in the function signature
- Colocate component, styles, and hooks in the same directory

```tsx
// ✅ Good
interface GenerationCardProps {
  generation: Generation;
  onSelect: (id: string) => void;
}

export function GenerationCard({ generation, onSelect }: GenerationCardProps) {
  return <div onClick={() => onSelect(generation.id)}>{generation.prompt}</div>;
}
```

## Hooks

- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks prefixed with `use`
- Keep hooks focused — one concern per hook
- Supabase queries should be wrapped in custom hooks, not called inline in components

## State

- Prefer local state (`useState`) for UI-only state
- Use React context sparingly — only for truly global concerns (auth, theme)
- Derive state from existing state instead of syncing with `useEffect`

## Performance

- Memoize expensive computations with `useMemo`
- Wrap callback props with `useCallback` when passed to memoized children
- Never create objects/arrays inline in JSX props for memoized components
